        "prompt": "Design a comprehensive implementation plan for creating a **coding_guardrail.py** that manages post-plan coding workflow phases.\n\n## Goal\nReplace/extend `.claude/hooks/workflow/guardrail.py` with a new coding-focused guardrail activated by ExitPlanMode completion. This guardrail enforces TDD-based and non-TDD code workflows.\n\n## Workflow Requirements\n\n### TDD=true Flow:\n1. **write-tests** \u2192 TestEngineer creates tests\n2. **test-review** \u2192 TestReviewer reviews (Pass/Fail scoring, iterate max 3x)\n3. **write-code** \u2192 Main agent implements (no subagents, must pass tests)\n4. **validate** \u2192 QA expert validates acceptance criteria\n5. **pr-create** \u2192 Version manager creates PR\n\n### TDD=false Flow:\n1. **write-code** \u2192 Main agent implements directly\n2. **validate** \u2192 QA expert validates acceptance criteria\n3. **pr-create** \u2192 Version manager creates PR\n\n## Existing Architecture (to leverage)\n\n### Key Files:\n- **plan_guardrail.py** (424 lines) \u2014 Self-contained guardrail with inline handlers\n- **guards/** \u2014 Modular validation files (agent_guard, review_guard, write_guard, bash_guard, stop_guard, phase_guard)\n- **state_store.py** \u2014 File-locked JSON persistence\n- **hook.py** \u2014 Hook utility class (read_stdin, advanced_block, system_message)\n- **dispatchers/plan_guardrail/** \u2014 4 Python scripts per hook event\n\n### Reusable Helpers:\n- `parse_scores()` from review_guard.py \u2014 extract confidence/quality from text\n- `count_completed()` from agent_guard.py \u2014 count completed agents by type\n- `advance_next_phase()` from review_guard.py \u2014 mark phase done, next in_progress\n- PHASE_RULES dict pattern \u2014 define allowed agents per phase\n- FileManager with locking from lib/file_manager.py\n\n## Design Constraints\n\n1. **Activation Trigger**: PostToolUse of ExitPlanMode signals plan acceptance \u2192 initialize coding_workflow state\n2. **State Structure**: Store under `state[\"coding_workflow\"]` key (parallel to `state[\"plan_workflow\"]`)\n3. **Test Reviewer Scoring**: Parse \"Pass\" or \"Fail\" only (not numeric scores)\n4. **TDD Branching**: At activation, check TDD flag and skip write-tests/test-review phases if false\n5. **Main Agent Coding**: write-code phase blocks ALL subagents (main agent writes directly)\n6. **Phase Transitions**: Auto-advance when completion criteria met\n7. **Guardrails**: Block premature PR creation, code writing, and stopping\n\n## Plan Requirements\n\nYour plan must include:\n\n1. **Files to Create/Modify** \u2014 List each file with action (Create/Edit/Delete)\n2. **State Structure** \u2014 Show the coding_workflow JSON schema with all phases\n3. **coding_guardrail.py Structure** \u2014 Outline all handlers (PreToolUse Agent/Write/Bash, PostToolUse ExitPlanMode, SubagentStop, Stop)\n4. **Phase Rules** \u2014 Define allowed agents per phase, ordering constraints\n5. **Dispatcher Files** \u2014 Show dispatcher structure in dispatchers/coding_guardrail/\n6. **Activation Logic** \u2014 How ExitPlanMode PostToolUse initializes coding workflow\n7. **TDD Branching** \u2014 How to skip phases when TDD=false\n8. **Test Review Scoring** \u2014 How to parse \"Pass\"/\"Fail\" and iterate\n9. **Verification Strategy** \u2014 How to test end-to-end without breaking existing plan workflow\n\n## Context from Research\n\n- **Hooks Available**: PreToolUse (Agent, Write, Bash, ExitPlanMode), PostToolUse (ExitPlanMode), SubagentStop, Stop\n- **Pattern**: Dispatchers call guardrail.py via subprocess with JSON input, parse result\n- **JSON Output**: PreToolUse uses `hookSpecificOutput.permissionDecision`, others use top-level `decision: \"block\"`\n- **Exit Codes**: 0 for success (with JSON or text), 2 for block with message\n- **Infinite Loop Prevention**: Check `stop_hook_active` in Stop/SubagentStop hooks\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nYour plan should be:\n- **Specific**: Name all files, show code structure outlines\n- **Feasible**: Leverage existing helpers, follow proven patterns\n- **Clear**: Explain state flow, phase transitions, blocking rules\n- **Testable**: Include verification approach that doesn't break existing workflow",
